    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down. | Bromley. | Kent. S.E.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>Mar 12.</date>
                    <salute>My dear Huxley</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I read Lushington’s letter in a rather hurried manner, as if it had been a printed essay &amp; not addressed to you; &amp; I suppose in consequence of this the offensive passages did not strike me.<ref target="#foot.f2"/> Now that they are pointed out I fully agree that he had no right to address them to you; &amp; this I have now told him.<ref target="#foot.f3"/> Assuredly if I had noticed these passages I sh<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> have refused to be the channel of communication. I suspect when M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Lushington urges you to <hi rend="underline">read</hi> Comte<ref target="#foot.f4"/> he meant to express to study &amp; digest his works. Red-hot disciples do not weigh their words when their master is attacked, &amp; on this plea I hope you will make some allowance. I feel sure that I need not tell you that you are about the last man in England towards whom I w<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> consciously offer myself as a channel of offence.</p>
<p>This note requires no answer.</p>
<p>ever yours most truly | Charles Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
        </div>

        

        

